The 'gooseneck' is the swivel connection on a sailboat by which the boom
attaches to the mast. The boom moves from side to side and up and down by
swiveling on the gooseneck.

The gooseneck may be a two axis swivel as pictured. Having an integrated shackle
for the tack is common. Goosenecks on older rigs may be formed by a loop
attached to the end of the boom that fits loosely about the mast.
